# e9cd030c12244b02a4eba7f592ff8361
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/ts-markup.en.rst:109
msgid "Statistics"
msgstr ""

# 2fddaa925c5542ec9bc64c9b1a67809f
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/ts-markup.en.rst:111
msgid ""
"|TS| statistics are documented using the domain ``:ts:stat:``. The domain"
" takes three required arguments (collection, name, data type) and an "
"option fourth (an example value). ::"
msgstr ""

# 8aaff08851d849d69367055b93c28e56
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/ts-markup.en.rst:123
msgid "Collection"
msgstr ""

# 9ba5c913651d41798a7c8bc4f872d52f
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/ts-markup.en.rst:121
msgid ""
"The key name of the collection in the returned JSON data from the :ref"
":`plugin-stats-over-http` plugin. For most statistics, this is the "
"literal sting :literal:`global`. *Required*"
msgstr ""

# 822548e6c3cf4ce69cd7f481f8a3f52e
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/ts-markup.en.rst:126
msgid "Statistic Name"
msgstr ""

# 24101d4ca77f44deb7b64024ba26fefd
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/ts-markup.en.rst:126
msgid "The exact and full name of the statistic. *Required*"
msgstr ""

# 1df0ce9ebf3f489eb7efd0bdec4daec8
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/ts-markup.en.rst:129
msgid ""
"One of the following literal string values: :literal:`integer`, "
":literal:`float`, :literal:`boolean`, or :literal:`string`. *Required*"
msgstr ""

# e7ac03ce1f1a4e679012bacc5a1dea87
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/ts-markup.en.rst:137
msgid "Example Value"
msgstr ""

# 9464e59f30ee4170baf77d3500e9b6ef
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/ts-markup.en.rst:133
msgid ""
"A valid example of the value which may be exported by the statistic. In "
"cases where the description of the statistic makes note of particular "
"features of the values, such as the case of string statistics which may "
"be formatted in specific ways, providing the optional example is strongly"
" recommended. *Optional*"
msgstr ""

# d28611c2eeb246ab9101d00ce64028f6
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/ts-markup.en.rst:139
msgid ""
"The statistics domain also supports several options which can provide "
"even more metadata about the statistic. These are currently:"
msgstr ""

# 315c0b446fc643afad314312fb4bd60b
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/ts-markup.en.rst:172
msgid "type"
msgstr ""

# 370a0b0a27c5406ca8486a795c97397c
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/ts-markup.en.rst:146
msgid "Defines the type of metric exposed by the statistic. Valid values are:"
msgstr ""

# d6ac0dddfb86443ea53bc129bd12f554
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/ts-markup.en.rst:151
msgid ":literal:`counter`"
msgstr ""

# 92a4deae2f6f4964bfa0699cfd497bfe
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/ts-markup.en.rst:149
msgid ""
"Numeric values which only increment based on the accumulation or "
"occurrence of underlying events. Examples include the total number of "
"incoming connections, or the total number of bytes transferred."
msgstr ""

# f633829de967483fbdca32bef86b2dbe
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/ts-markup.en.rst:156
msgid ":literal:`gauge`"
msgstr ""

# 6c3d35efb0434b92b41629e7453a2006
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/ts-markup.en.rst:154
msgid ""
"Used for moment-in-time metrics, such as the current number of |TS| "
"processes running, or the current number of connections open to origin "
"servers."
msgstr ""

# a500dfaa434d4d69aa8a4188267b4f70
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/ts-markup.en.rst:162
msgid ":literal:`flag`"
msgstr ""

# db683e067fcb4c5cbcc6b180230f8fb4
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/ts-markup.en.rst:159
msgid ""
"Indicates that values for this statistic will be an integer with each "
"value indicating a particular state. Most statistics of this type are "
"booleans, where :literal:`1` indicates a truth or an *on* state, and "
":literal:`0` the opposite."
msgstr ""

# 79b5b8ad6639422a9a6faefedfc0383e
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/ts-markup.en.rst:172
msgid ":literal:`derivative`"
msgstr ""

# fc831daa96634ecd8353d77f649e2d6c
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/ts-markup.en.rst:165
msgid ""
"Statistics of this type presents values that are calculated, or derived, "
"from other staistics. They do not expose a number or state gathered "
"directly. Typical statistics of this type are representations of a "
"statistic over a given period (e.g. average origin connections per "
"second), ratio or percentage of a statistic as part of a set (e.g. the "
"percentage of total dns lookups which have failed), or any other "
"statistic whose computation depends on the value(s) of one or more other "
"statistics."
msgstr ""

# 7b0cacb9c8b946b78fd88364f0995e85
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/ts-markup.en.rst:176
msgid "unit"
msgstr ""

# e8272ff127a14af28ce17c7830bbee43
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/ts-markup.en.rst:175
msgid ""
"Indicates the units of measurement that should be assumed for the given "
"statistic's value."
msgstr ""

# ff92bc948d414346a56e63583ebc8a8a
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/ts-markup.en.rst:181
msgid "introduced"
msgstr ""

# 2a3757a9a7d547ca9b281ead6f0f73a5
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/ts-markup.en.rst:179
msgid ""
"May be used to indicate the version of |TS| in which the statistic was "
"first available. The value of this option should be a valid, human-"
"readable version number string, e.g. :literal:`5.3.0`."
msgstr ""

# 6b5a734013fe49deb8926dbfa00c4602
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/ts-markup.en.rst:184
msgid ""
"Used to indicate that the statistic is no longer supported and may be "
"removed in later versions. This option may be used as a simple flag "
"without any given value, or may have a value associated in which case it "
"should be a valid, human-readable version number string for the |TS| "
"release which was first to deprecate the statistic."
msgstr ""

# e1904af2d79046a9abe72e79c6b97dc0
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/ts-markup.en.rst:194
msgid "ungathered"
msgstr ""

# 47aae9310faf4944800da98a581ab96c
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/ts-markup.en.rst:191
msgid ""
"A simple flag option, without any associated values, indicating that "
"while the statistic is included in the output of plugins like :ref"
":`plugin-stats-over-http` there is no underlying data gathered for the "
"statistic. If a statistic is thus marked, it should be assumed to be "
"invalid or simply unimplemented."
msgstr ""

# afd5ce7d077e487789b78c3eed7cfd68
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/ts-markup.en.rst:199
msgid ""
"To reference a statistic from elsewhere in the documentation, the "
"standard domain reference markup should be used::"
msgstr ""

# aed8e349ba3a47608c86a641e40a7bc0
#: ../../developer-guide/documentation/ts-markup.en.rst:204
msgid ""
"References should not include the collection name, data type, or any "
"other components aside from the statistic name."
msgstr ""

